In this statement, the President commemorates Armenian Remembrance Day and acknowledges the Meds Yeghern, one of the worst atrocities of the 20th century, in which 1.5 million Armenians were killed or marched to their deaths. The President emphasizes the importance of reflecting on the lives lost and the suffering endured, and expresses the commitment to ensuring that such dark chapters of history are not repeated. He also states his own view on the events of 1915 and emphasizes the need for a full and just acknowledgement of the facts. The President recognizes the indomitable spirit and resilience of the Armenian people and the contributions of Armenian-Americans to the United States. He expresses support for the Armenian people in their efforts to build a nation that cherishes democracy and respect for human liberty and dignity. The statement concludes by affirming the enduring commitment to the people of Armenia.